<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pearson</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-01"><hi rend="italic">November 1,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Pearson reports that the Crown Prince has informed the minister for
                            foreign affairs that six accomplices, endeavoring to escape, were killed
                            by the Persian forces, and that the remainder of the band is being
                            pursued.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>